    "body": "### Problem\n\nUsing MeslLGS Nerd Font in kitty terminal\nitalic in font selection looks fine\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/13bc61b6-e282-44e2-afff-5642de3c1cef)\nbut in neovim it does not render italic M,N symbols in full\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f8d985e9-59f0-48ae-b3a6-1400c84dd0ec)\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nAs I said already, terminal is kitty, font is MesloLGS Nerd Font Mono\n\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, \"Comment\", { italic = true })\n-- My comment to showcase issue MNMNMNMNM\n```\nExecute\nnvim example.lua -u example.lua\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nfont spacing or whatever it is should be the same as in the terminal\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, 9.1\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux x86_64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
